HEADWORD: outfangthef
<hw>out*fang"thef</hw> <pr>(out*f⟦acr⟧ng"th⟦ecr⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[AS. <ets>⟦umac⟧t-fangen-⟦thorn⟧e⟦oacute⟧f</ets>. See <er>Out</er>,
<er>Fang</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, and <er>Thief</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anglo-Saxon & O. Eng. Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A thief from
without or abroad, taken within a lord's fee or liberty.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The privilege of trying such a thief.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
